          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="content-guidelines" class="doc-h3">Content Guidelines<span class="h3-badge" style="background:rgba(37,99,235,0.1);color:var(--prism-violet);">Recommended</span></h3>
            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span><ul>
                <li>Keep navigation labels concise and recognizable (1&#8211;2 words).</li>
                <li>Use the correct variant for the product's navigation architecture.</li>
                <li>Always show the active tab state so users know where they are.</li>
                <li>Turn off unused Nav slots to prevent empty spacing in the tab row.</li>
              </ul></div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span><ul>
                <li>Use long multi-word labels that cause tab overflow prematurely.</li>
                <li>Use the Endpoint Central variant in a left-nav product or vice versa.</li>
                <li>Leave all tabs in the inactive state &#8212; users lose wayfinding context.</li>
                <li>Hide search purely for visual tidiness &#8212; it is a core utility.</li>
              </ul></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

