          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="when-to-use" class="doc-section-title">When and Where to Use</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">The Header Navigation is the primary persistent chrome for every product page.</p>
            <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:24px;margin-top:24px;">
              <div style="padding:24px;background:var(--prism-surface);border:1px solid var(--prism-border);border-radius:12px;">
                <h3 style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);margin-bottom:16px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#2563eb" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>When to use</h3>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border:none;background:transparent;padding-left:20px;font-size:14.5px;">
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">As the single persistent top bar for every page in a product.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">Use <strong>Endpoint Central</strong> when the product has top-level horizontal navigation (8 items or fewer).</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;">Use the left-nav variants (<strong>EC left only</strong>, <strong>MDM</strong>, <strong>Patch Manager Plus</strong>) when primary navigation is in a left sidebar.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div style="padding:24px;background:var(--prism-surface);border:1px solid var(--prism-border);border-radius:12px;">
                <h3 style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);margin-bottom:16px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#e42527" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>When NOT to use</h3>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border:none;background:transparent;padding-left:20px;font-size:14.5px;">
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">As a secondary navigation bar within a page &#8212; use Tabs or a Section Header instead.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">Inside a modal or flyout &#8212; navigation is not needed inside overlay contexts.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;">As a mobile top bar &#8212; this component is designed for desktop/1440px viewports.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="alignment-placement" class="doc-section-title">Alignment &amp; Placement</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Consistent placement ensures predictable navigation across all products.</p>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Position:</strong> Always fixed at the top of the viewport. The header persists across all page scrolls.</li>
              <li><strong>Width:</strong> Full viewport width (1440px design, stretches to container).</li>
              <li><strong>Z-index:</strong> Above all page content. Modals and drawers may overlay the header.</li>
              <li><strong>Logo zone:</strong> Always at the far left. The product icon and name are not interactive beyond acting as a home link.</li>
              <li><strong>Utility cluster:</strong> Always at the far right. Icon order is consistent across all variants.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="detailed-guidelines" class="doc-section-title">Complete Do's and Don'ts</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Guidelines for effective header navigation usage.</p>
            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span><ul>
                <li><strong>Match the variant to the product:</strong> Use Endpoint Central for top-nav products, left-nav variants for sidebar products.</li>
                <li><strong>Keep Nav slot count accurate:</strong> Turn off unused Nav N props to avoid empty spacing.</li>
                <li><strong>Show Customer Selector for multi-tenant:</strong> It allows switching between tenants/accounts.</li>
                <li><strong>Set the correct active tab:</strong> Coordinate with the current page to show the right active state.</li>
                <li><strong>Keep search visible:</strong> Only use Show Search=OFF when search is genuinely unavailable.</li>
              </ul></div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span><ul>
                <li><strong>Don't leave unused Nav slots ON:</strong> They create empty spacing in the tab row.</li>
                <li><strong>Don't mix navigation architectures:</strong> Using Endpoint Central in a left-nav product creates confusion.</li>
                <li><strong>Don't show Customer Selector in single-tenant:</strong> It is unnecessary for personal-account products.</li>
                <li><strong>Don't leave all tabs inactive:</strong> Users lose wayfinding context without an active indicator.</li>
                <li><strong>Don't hide search for aesthetics:</strong> Search is a core utility expected by users.</li>
              </ul></div>
            </div>
          </div>
